# C++ ↔ C# Model Parity

`src/models/*.{h,hpp}` is the **source of truth**. `abstractions/src/Models/*.cs` must mirror every serialized field.
Whenever you change a model on either side, update the other in the same PR.

## File mapping

| C++ (`src/models/`) | C# (`abstractions/src/Models/`) |
|---|---|
| `CommonTypes.hpp` | `CommonTypes.cs` |
| `SignatureValidation.hpp` | `SignatureValidation.cs` |
| `ProductDetection.hpp` | `ProductDetection.cs` |
| `DownloadLocationConfig.h` | `DownloadLocationConfig.cs` |
| `SharedConfig.hpp` | `SharedConfig.cs` |
| `MergedConfig.hpp` | `MergedConfig.cs` |
| `UpdateRelease.hpp` | `UpdateRelease.cs` |
| `UpdateConfig.hpp` | `UpdateConfig.cs` |
| `UpdateResponse.hpp` | `UpdateResponse.cs` |
| `InstanceConfig.hpp` | `InstanceConfig.cs` |

## Naming contract

- C# properties are **PascalCase**; they serialize to the **camelCase** field names used in the C++
  `NLOHMANN_DEFINE_TYPE_NON_INTRUSIVE_WITH_DEFAULT` macros (the schema endpoint applies
  `CamelCasePropertyNamesContractResolver` globally).
- Enum member names must match `magic_enum::enum_name` output **exactly** (same casing, e.g. `WhenPresent`,
  `FromUpdaterBinary`). Use `[EnumMember(Value = nameof(...))]` on the C# side.

## Serialized-member checklist

When adding or removing a serialized member:

1. **C++ side**: update both the class body **and** the `NLOHMANN_DEFINE_TYPE_*` argument list.
2. **C# side**: add/remove the property and update XML doc comments.
3. **`SharedConfig` / `MergedConfig`** are intentionally kept in sync with each other
   (see `\remarks Keep in sync with …` in both files). Update both when either changes.
4. Only fields listed in the C++ serializer macro cross the wire — runtime-only members of
   `InstanceConfig` (window handle, task handle, etc.) must **not** appear in the C# model.
